(17236, 'propafenone hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Coadministration of propafenone with drugs metabolized by CYP2D6 (such as desipramine, imipramine, haloperidol, venlafaxine) might lead to increased plasma concentrations of these drugs.', 'DailyMed'),
