(17236, 'desvenlafaxine er', 'N/A', 'contraindicated', '7.1 Drugs Having Clinically Important Interactions with Desvenlafaxine Table 8: Clinically Important Drug Interactions with Desvenlafaxine Monoamine Oxidase Inhibitors (MAOI) Clinical Impact The concomitant use of SSRIs and SNRIs including desvenlafaxine with MAOIs increases the risk of serotonin syndrome. Intervention Concomitant use of desvenlafaxine is contraindicated: ● With an MAOI intended to treat psychiatric disorders or within 7 days of stopping treatment with desvenlafaxine. Examples selegiline, tranylcypromine, isocarboxazid, phenelzine, linezolid, methylene blue Other Serotonergic Drugs Clinical Impact Concomitant use of desvenlafaxine with other serotonergic drugs increases the risk of serotonin syndrome.', 'DailyMed'),
