(32909, 'abacavir sulfate, dolutegravir sodium, lamivudine', 'N/A', 'minor', 'Dolutegravir may increase plasma concentrations of drugs eliminated via OCT2 or MATE1 (dofetilide, dalfampridine, and metformin) [see Contraindications (4), Drug Interactions (7.3)]. Metformina ↑Metformin Refer to the prescribing information for metformin for assessing the benefit and risk of concomitant use of TRIUMEQ or TRIUMEQ PD and metformin.', 'DailyMed'),
