(4467, 'saxagliptin and metformin hydrochloride', 'N/A', 'major', '7 DRUG INTERACTIONS Strong CYP3A4/5 inhibitors (e.g., ketoconazole): Coadministration with saxagliptin and metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets significantly increases saxagliptin concentrations. Limit saxagliptin and metformin hydrochloride extended-release tablets dosage to 2.5 mg/1,000 mg once daily when coadministered with a strong CYP3A4/5 inhibitor. (7.2) Drugs that reduce metformin clearance: May increase risk of lactic acidosis.', 'DailyMed'),
